# OSLIFE · cognee worker — copy to .env, fill in, then `docker-compose up -d`.
# Never commit the filled-in file.

# ── cognee's own LLM (required — it calls an LLM itself to extract entities/
# relationships during remember()). This is a SEPARATE key/cost from OSLIFE's
# own ANTHROPIC_API_KEY / VOYAGE_API_KEY — cognee's documented, verified
# config is OpenAI:
LLM_API_KEY=
LLM_PROVIDER=openai
LLM_MODEL=openai/gpt-5-mini
EMBEDDING_PROVIDER=openai
EMBEDDING_MODEL=openai/text-embedding-3-small
#
# cognee is litellm-based, so Anthropic *may* work via the lines below instead
# — UNVERIFIED, not in cognee's own documented examples, try at your own risk
# and fall back to the OpenAI config above if remember()/search calls fail:
#LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic
#LLM_MODEL=anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
#LLM_API_KEY=<same value as OSLIFE's own ANTHROPIC_API_KEY>

# ── Shared secret the Caddy proxy checks on every request. Generate with
# `openssl rand -base64 32`. The SAME value goes on the cognee-remember /
# cognee-search Supabase Edge Function secrets (see docs/SECRETS.md).
COGNEE_WORKER_SECRET=
